pageContext.claim: “ICE is doing that job. These are brave people. They go into towns in Long Island, where I grew up, right next to these places, I know them all. They used to be, you'd leave your door open, you'd, leave your window open. You go to sleep, nobody thinks. Now you -- it's like a fort, but not anymore.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump grew up in Queens (technically but not colloquially "Long Island"). Despite the presence of MS-13 on Long Island, Trump exaggerates by saying residents turned it into a "fort."
